---
name: scljet-write-index
description: SclJet index writer — a rowid table plus a single-column index B-tree that reference SQLite validates and uses (cross-backend)
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet index writer

[ByteSlice, byteSliceToList, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableWithIndexDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)

```scalascript
// A rowid table whose `n` column is out of order, plus an index on `n`. The index
// is a separate B-tree (page kind 10) of (n, rowid) records sorted by (n, rowid).
// Reference integrity_check cross-checks the index against the table — a passing
// file proves the index is correct — and the query planner uses it. int and JS
// produce the same bytes.
val rows = List(
  List(SqlInteger(30L), SqlText("thirty")),
  List(SqlInteger(10L), SqlText("ten")),
  List(SqlInteger(20L), SqlText("twenty")),
  List(SqlInteger(5L), SqlText("five")),
  List(SqlInteger(25L), SqlText("twentyfive")))

buildTableWithIndexDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(n INTEGER, v TEXT)",
  "idx", "CREATE INDEX idx ON t(n)", List(0), rows) match
  case Right(bytes) => println((bytes.length / 512).toString + ":" + byteSliceToList(bytes).toString)
  case Left(error) => println("ERROR:" + error.message)
```
